data.title: Roy Acuff
authors: Contributors to Old Time and Bluegrass Wiki
data.meta_description: Roy Claxton Acuff (born September 15, 1903 – died November 23, 1992) was an American country music singer, fiddler, and promoter. Also Known as the "King of Country Music. Roy Acuff was born in Maynardville, Tennessee to Ida and Simon E. Neill Acuff, the third of five children.
data.text: Roy Claxton Acuff (born September 15, 1903 – died November 23, 1992) was an American country music singer, fiddler, and promoter. Also Known as the "King of Country Music. Roy Acuff was born in Maynardville, Tennessee to Ida and Simon E. Neill Acuff, the third of five children.
